STIBS2.intro: Powerful control panels, clever fire detectors and smart peripheral devices.
STIBS2.description: The front end of the STIBS2CC project is implemented with the Angular Framework and runs on the client's browser. The Angular CLI is used in conjunction with NodeJs to develop the project.Every user has to authenticate himself via the login mask. Only then are the functions of the application available to him.
requirement: detailed information on commissioning progress down to the protocol level.
Overview of the fleet: online status, direct forwarding from the CC to the test computer.
Redmine connection for mapping serial defects.
Overview page for comments/remarks.
Central update and test configuration distribution.
Automated creation of final reports
STIBS2.overview: The navigation should enable the user to navigate between the individual components of the front end.The dashboard is the main page of the application and contains overviews of the test results of the currently selected project in the header.A pie chart shows the test status of the selected project.The data of the history and performance components can be restricted using the filter.The database upload should offer the possibility of importing configuration and test results databases into the central server.User administration and archiving process should also be implemented.
